medical_history.chief_complaint: Urinary incontinence developed suddenly six months earlier.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The urinary incontinence began suddenly six months prior to the visit. One month after the onset, the patient sought medical attention.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The patient had breast cancer 22 years earlier, treated with radical mastectomy and chemotherapy.
medical_history.family_history: The patient's sister had breast cancer followed by ovarian cancer. The mother had lung cancer. Two maternal uncles had pancreatic cancer, a maternal aunt had myeloma, and her maternal grandmother had uterine cancer. Genetic testing indicated a missense mutation in BRCA1.
